title: For Sale:  Taurus Raging Hornet .22 Hornet 8 Shot Revolver
postcontent:
Try something powerful and accurate!  This gun is big and beautiful, a real eye catcher, when my friends see it,  they all wants their picture taken holding it. My collection no longer comes even close to fitting in my gun safe,  I need to make more room, so I'm looking to sell the Raging Hornet. It's by far the most accurate handgun I've come across.  The gun is in great condition, barrel is bright and tight, rifling is sharp and no crud or pockmarks, lock up is tight and positive, trigger is excellent. There is no wear and tear from  travel or carry, it only went from the safe to my home range and back to the safe. 

The Raging Hornet is an 8 shot, DA/SA revolver in .22 Hornet. It has adjustable front and rear sights and a dove 

tail for mounting optics. The cylinder uses a double lock at the front and the rear of the cylinder, providing a really solid lock up. The full length extractor ejects the cases. 

Sale includes the Taurus Raging Hornet, matching scope mount, matching scope 1.5-4x, the original box, keys, manual, and about 75 rounds of ammo. Also included is a mint copy of Guns & Ammo featuring the Raging Hornet on the cover, as well as a sweet Raging Hornet lapel pin.

The thing I love about the Raging Hornet is the caliber.22 Hornet, it's more powerful than I realized. It holds 8 rounds in the cylinder and the trigger is beautiful for both single and double action.  It shoots flat and hits hard, it's a handgun a sniper would love. A word of caution, on my range the Raging Hornet puts a massive dent in the metal targets I use for handguns. 

Locations is Lebanon Maine, buyer pays any shipping and FFL fees.

postcontent:
For sale is a 1971 Ruger Model 1 .22-250 single shot, falling block rifle. The serial number is 130-02678, indicating it was manufactured in 1971. Currently there are Williams Aperature sights on the rifle, however it has a bridge for scope rings. There are front and rear points for a sling. There is a spacer between the recoil pad and the stock. The barrel is 22".

Overall the rifle is in excellent visual conditional and excellent mechanical condition. I consider the wood to be 95%, meaning if you look hard you can find a couple of light nicks and scratches. The bluing is still in great shape, but a little faded on the ejector handle. The action feels flawless, it is smooth and tight. I really love the trigger - no creep, just a light, crisp break. This is an excellent long range rifle, the .22-250 round is blazing fast - 3500-4000 FPS muzzle velocity depending on the grain and brand of round. It has much less drop at long ranges (300 yards+) than the more popular .308, .270 or 30-06.

title: For Sale:  SPRINGFIELD M1 GARAND WWII -- 10-44 Bbl
postcontent: The greatest battle implement ever devised."...here's a Springfield Armory M1 Garand semi-automatic rifle that was manufactured during WWII in late 1944. Chambered for the .30-06 Springfield cartridge, the gas-operated Garand is fed via an 8-shot spring steel en-bloc clip. This rifle wears the original 10-44 dated Springfield barrel and nearly all of the parts are WWII Springfield manufacture from the late war period. The safety lever dates from about 1942. The rear sight is the correct long pinion with type III square-end lock bar. The curved-side op rod is uncut. This rifle is in overall good condition with normal wear from military service. It appears the metal finish was likely reparked as the barrel breech face is not bright, but there is no chrome on the barrel gas port. The stock shows a few dings and dents but there are no cracks. A very faint small crossed cannons cartouche is visible on the left side of the stock. There is a single "P" proof on the grip and there is an "A4" stamped on the left side of the butt. The mechanics appear to be in good working order. The bore rates very good with bright, sharp rifling that shows some slight frost in the grooves but good solid muzzle and throat erosion readings. There are NO import markings on this rifle

The Geissele Super Dynamic - 3 Gun (SD-3G) trigger is a semi-automatic-only derivative of the two-stage Super Select-Fire (SSF) combat trigger that Geissele Automatics produces for customers in the U.S. Special Operations Community. The SD-3G was developed to combine the SSF combat trigger’s match-grade semi-automatic performance with its smooth single-stage full-automatic feel to make a fast, smooth, and robust trigger ideal for 3 Gun competition shooting. The new Geissele Super Dynamic - 3 Gun trigger has a super short trigger pull and a short reset so that rounds can be sent
downrange as quickly as possible while still maintaining superb accuracy. 

The Super Dynamic Triggers are rugged, non-adjustable combat triggers with a sear design that provides a wide margin of safety against unintentional discharges yet still gives the operator a sharp, repeatable trigger release.
